evidence:
POC Execution Output:
The POC successfully identified 2 email input fields missing the autocomplete="off" attribute:

1. Found at: http://localhost:8080/
   HTML: &lt;input type="email" class="form-control" id="email" name="email" required&gt;

2. Found at: http://localhost:8080/index.html
   HTML: &lt;input type="email" class="form-control" id="email" name="email" required&gt;

Both fields are identical and lack the autocomplete="off" attribute, allowing browser auto-fill functionality to cache and suggest previously entered email addresses. The POC scanned multiple common endpoints and confirmed the vulnerability at the root level endpoints.

Current vulnerable HTML:
&lt;input type="email" class="form-control" id="email" name="email" required&gt;

This field allows browser autocomplete to populate with cached email addresses, creating a password manager and browser history exposure vulnerability on shared systems.
